rComments: Is not very helpful, teaches the class as if we are familiar with all the biological terms... As my friend (A  biology major said) : "She is the worst teacher to put in a biology course for non-biology students"
Maria Arts was a good professor.  Her labs were interesting and fun, and tests were easy as long as you studied well for them.  Absolutely no trick questions.
just runs through her powerpoints and doesnt sound like she knows what she's teaching

She would go through the material very fast and eventhough people could ask her to slow down she would continue with her own pace.  She was not understanding and her test were all over the place.  he marking scheme was not understandable.  Don't take her class!

Her test questions are completely incomprehensible....most of the ta's under her organization just use their own marking scheme for labs...she ruined my second year...the average for her labs and her tests is a fail!  her tests are just not valid....

For people who commented on Bio 153, it is not that the prof is bad, but the COURSE IS HORRIBLE. I have had her for 204, and believe me when i say this: she is the most approachable prof you will ever meet in university (especially in the Bio dept).
